# Response Format

## General

- Max 2–3 sentences of explanation before showing code
- Show only changed lines for edits — not full file rewrites unless file is new
- No "Here's what I did" summaries unless the user asks
- No emoji unless user requests it
- No unnecessary padding or filler text

## Step Format (for multi-step tasks)

```
Step 1/4 — Creating leads.service.ts
Step 2/4 — Updating LeadsTable imports
Step 3/4 — Deleting legacy component
Step 4/4 — Verifying no remaining imports
```

## Verification Format

```
✓ No remaining api-client-react imports in modules/
✓ All 8 admin routes respond 401 without cookie
✓ Seed: 8 projects, 6 services, 8 leads inserted
```

## Error Format

```
✗ BrandingManager still imports useToast → replaced with sonner
✗ Migration failed: column already exists → skipped, no schema change needed
```

## Code Output

- Always cite file path above code blocks
- Use CODE REFERENCES format for existing code
- Use MARKDOWN CODE BLOCKS for new code proposals
- Never include line numbers in code block content

## Phase Completion Report

When finishing a phase, output a short table:

| Item | Count | Status |
|------|-------|--------|
| Files created | N | ✅ |
| Files deleted | N | ✅ |
| DB migration | yes/no | ✅ |
| Swagger updated | yes/no | ✅ |
